Dan,<br><br>
Hello, once again.  I've know vets who have had good and not so good experiences with the VA and VFW.  We have a real good VSO (Veteran's Service Officer -- county job) where I live and he seems to make the difference for vets with  paperwork and resources in the area.  It is not easy, and you have to decide what efforts you want to make in this regard.<br><br>
When I first read about Agent Orange in the 1980s I went to my personal physician with questions.  I gave him and he read the book -- WAITING FOR AN ARMY TO DIE, and then we talked.  We both tried to find a place that was doing biopsies for dioxin at the time, but couldn't find anyone -- not even the CDC.  I was stationed in Cu Chi in 1967 and had/ have reason to be concerned, but that's another story.<br><br>
I wish you well with the rest of your life and your swimming pool.  The guys on this site will pop in and out and I know am speaking for them when I wish you the best.<br><br>
Paul<br>

